import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.countplot(x="Species", data=data)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of species in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Beak_Length__mm_', y='Beak_Depth__mm_')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between beak length and beak depth?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Body_Mass__g_')
    plt.axvline(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="Island", y="Beak_Length__mm_", data=data)
    chart.axhline(data['Beak_Length__mm_'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Beak_Length__mm_'].median()))
    chart.set_title('What is the distribution of beak length by island?', wrap=True)
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
